Click on Create new jobs. Following are the five steps in building jobs:
General description
Source code management
build triggers
build steps
post build actions


Give the required details and build the jobs.
In Souce code management we can give GIT details for our project and build it.
We can also install Nexus plugin in Jenkins and give our nexus repository URL to save the artifacts generated(jar files) directly at our speified location as a build job action.

Second way of building jobs is through scripting which is called pipeline.
Click on New Item --> Enter a name --> select pipeline --> OK
it has the following four steps:
General description
build triggers
Advance Project options
pipeline

Two ways of pipeline:
Scripted pipeline

Declarative pipeline
